# LoC budget exceptions (used by scripts/enforce-budgets.js).
#
# Format per line: <relative-path>  <reason>
# Lines starting with '#' are comments. Only the first whitespace-separated
# field is read as the path; the rest is informational rationale.
#
# Each entry MUST justify why splitting the file would harm the codebase.
# The default expectation is to refactor, not to ignore.

# Phaser Scene subclass. The class implements the Phaser lifecycle contract
# (preload/create/update + a large public surface consumed by manager helpers
# in apps/web/src/game/{map,editor,camera}). It already delegates heavily to
# manager classes; further extraction would create hidden `this`-binding
# coupling via mixins or partial-class workarounds, which violates the
# lifecycle contract. Recommendation tracked in AGENTS.md to raise the
# Phaser-scene absolute budget to 800 LoC.
apps/web/src/game/scenes/MainScene.ts  phaser-scene delegation pattern, splitting breaks lifecycle contract

# Composite hook that wires multiple sub-hooks unconditionally per React
# hook-call-order rules. The function body is long because every sub-hook
# must be invoked in the same render pass; splitting into multiple component
# bodies would create the same wiring elsewhere without reducing complexity.
apps/web/src/app/routes/hooks/useWorldHooksComposite.ts  react hook-order constraint prevents body split

# Composite hook (useAvStateSync) that wires AV reactivity subscribers in a
# single render pass; same hook-order rationale as useWorldHooksComposite.
# 123 LoC, three above the 120-line hook limit. The body is a linear sequence
# of useEffect subscriptions where every branch must run on every render.
apps/web/src/app/routes/hooks/useAvStateSync.ts  react hook-order constraint, body is a linear effect sequence

# Editor message handler dispatch: one function that switches on the Colyseus
# editor message type and routes to the matching reducer action. Splitting
# the switch would scatter the dispatch contract across files. 94 LoC.
apps/web/src/realtime/handlers/editorHandlers.ts  message-dispatch switch kept as a single unit

# ExpandedCard JSX return body (156 LoC, six over the 150-line tsx limit).
# A single declarative JSX tree that composes avatar, name plate, volume
# meter, status badges, and the video element. Extracting fragments produces
# helper components with one consumer; the inline form is more readable.
apps/web/src/ui/user/card/ExpandedCard.tsx  single declarative jsx tree, no real seams

# Map paint route handler (107 LoC, 27 over the 80-line default). A single
# cohesive request flow: schema parse, auth, layer lookup, chunk fetch,
# chunk update, persist, broadcast, wall side-effect, response. Each step
# is already extracted into a helper; what remains is the wiring.
apps/server/src/api/routes/maps.paint.ts  cohesive request flow, steps already extracted into helpers

# Tiled map JSON import route handler and the corresponding TMJ persistence
# helper. Both run a single end-to-end import pipeline that is best kept
# linear so the pre/post-conditions stay visible. Tmj.ts 200-296 and 323-407
# are 17 and 5 LoC over the default limit respectively.
apps/server/src/api/routes/tmj.ts  end-to-end tiled import flow, linearity preferred over premature extraction

# onJoin completion handler (82 LoC, 2 over the default limit) and onLeave
# lifecycle handler (86 LoC, 6 over the default limit). Critical-path room
# lifecycle code that the Colyseus contract expects as a single coherent
# function per event.
apps/server/src/rooms/lifecycle/onJoin.completion.ts  critical-path lifecycle, single coherent function
apps/server/src/rooms/lifecycle/onLeave.ts  critical-path lifecycle, single coherent function

# Local audio/video track lifecycle state machine (mic + cam). One cohesive
# class whose methods all operate on the same shared mutable state — the
# desired/published/pending flags, the republish/release timers and the
# _micOp/_camOp serialization promises — under one disposal contract (every
# method guards on _disposed and chains on the op promises). The I/O seams
# (getUserMedia + publish/unpublish) are ALREADY extracted into
# microphonePublishing.ts and cameraPublishing.ts; what remains is the stateful
# orchestration, which cannot be split without exposing that private mutable
# state across module boundaries or duplicating the concurrency/disposal guards,
# fracturing the very serialization guarantees the class exists to provide.
# 828 LoC.
apps/web/src/av/core/TrackManager.ts  av track lifecycle state machine, io seams already extracted
